I entered employment agency services for the first time when my former employer (a prestigious Latin American company) underwent major layoffs. As a contract employee who had worked for many years at the company I was especially vulnerable and the process of finding a job on the open job market was frustrating and discouraging. I send many (too many) applications but did not receive any reply at all. I did not understand why. After three months a human resources person at a large government agency explained to me about the differences between male and female employment agencies.
